---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: "How much investment do I need?",
    a: "We recommend you have £500 to start. You will need to buy a printer, labels, boxes and your stock from this amount. However, the more capital you invest, the more products you can source, and the more sales you'll make.",
  },
  {
    q: "How is this different to the Kickstarter Academy?",
    a: "The Kickstarter Academy is where we began teaching Amazon FBA. It's packed with unlimited one-on-one sessions over zoom with our experts with intensive support. While it's been a powerful launchpad for producing 6-Figure sellers, it was a privilege for financial blessed people with professional background who could comfortably afford to invest at least 5k, which not everyone can afford. The Amazon FBA Bootcamp on the other hand, it's a budget-friendly workshop with the goal of granting more people the opportunity to dive into Amazon FBA and have a shot of building their own 6-Figure FBA Business. It may not be on the same level as Kickstarter Academy, but it offers you the most affordable way to be coached by me and my expert team through 5 intensive sessions.",
  },
  {
    q: "Can I get a refund if I miss it or change my mind?",
    a: "Sadly since this is a Live programme, we cannot issue refunds. You can however transfer your place to somebody if for some reason you cannot attend. Email techsupport@makeymoney.co.uk for further support.",
  },
  {
    q: "Will this event be running again?",
    a: "This event might not happen again as it is a case-study programme to see if it can fulfill the desired purpose of providing affordable FBA Coaching. So we recommend that you attend this bootcamp and make the best out of it as you'll walk away with knowledge that'll open the door to starting your own profitable FBA Business.",
  },
  {
    q: "Will I need to use Alibaba?",
    a: "We're not going anywhere near the Risky Chinese Suppliers, we'll use UK-based suppliers only. This training teaches the wholesale and arbitrage model not private labelling, importing from abroad, and starting your own brand.",
  },
  {
    q: "What if I required more support after the bootcamp?",
    a: "You didn't think we'd just school you and let you figure the rest on your own did you? That's exactly why we include 90 days post bootcamp after-care support which includes: 1) 5 hours of intensive face to face Amazon FBA Strategy training. 2) A custom digital course packed with training videos, resources, and hand-holding advice, with lifetime access. 3) 90 days access to our private support group for 24/7 support. 4) 90 days worth of live group coaching calls covering leadership, business development, habit building, cost management, sourcing, and scaling. (These take place twice a week and they are recorded and placed into your portal incase you miss them.)",
  },
  {
    q: "When and where is the event taking place?",
    a: "The event is being held at London Chigwell Prince Regent Hotel, Manor Rd, Chigwell, Essex IG8 8AE. We have a swanky private room and lunch is included. You have the option to choose EITHER Saturday 2nd March 9.30–3.00pm or Sunday 3rd March 9.30–3.00pm. We are ALSO holding a business networking event on the evening of 2nd March at the same venue — so you're VERY likely to attend that too!",
  },
  {
    q: "How much money will I earn?",
    a: "That's not something we can answer or predict, how much money you're going to make depends heavily on how much effort you're going to put into your business. You might make few hundreds, thousands, a million or even a trillion! Any Coach that tells you something \"You're gonna hit your 10k per month very soon\" is someone selling you the dream for their own personal gain.",
  },
  {
    q: "What if I'm a beginner or already sell on Amazon?",
    a: "The purpose of this Bootcamp is to provide guidance and support to complete newbies who never sold or even heard of amazon FBA before, regardless of their education level or technical skills.",
  },
  {
    q: "I have more questions.",
    a: "Sure, if you have any questions related to the Bootcamp Training, email them to info@makeymoney.co.uk",
  },
];
---

<section class="faq" id="faq">
  <div class="faq-inner">
    <div class="faq-header">
      <h2 class="display-headline faq-headline reveal">
        Frequently Asked<br /><em>Questions.</em>
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-list">
      {faqs.map((item, i) => (
        <div class="faq-item reveal" style={`transition-delay: ${(i % 4) * 0.06}s`} data-faq>
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
            <span class="faq-q-num">{String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')}</span>
            <span class="faq-q-text">{item.q}</span>
            <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i></span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p class="faq-answer-text">{item.a}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="faq-still reveal">
      <div class="faq-still-rule"></div>
      <p class="faq-still-heading">Still have questions?</p>
      <p class="faq-still-sub">We're happy to help — reach out and we'll get back to you.</p>
      <a href="mailto:info@makeymoney.co.uk" class="faq-still-link">Email us directly</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq {
    background: var(--color-off-white);
    padding: 130px 0 110px;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .faq::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, rgba(26,26,26,0.15), transparent);
  }

  .faq-inner {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 60px;
    position: relative;
  }

  .faq-num {
    top: -40px;
    right: 0;
    color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.06);
  }

  .faq-header {
    margin-bottom: 72px;
  }

  .faq-headline {
    font-size: clamp(30px, 4vw, 56px);
    color: var(--color-near-black);
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .faq-headline em {
    color: var(--color-amazon);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* List */
  .faq-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.1);
  }

  .faq-item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.1);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .faq-question {
    width: 100%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 20px;
    padding: 28px 0;
    background: none;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    text-align: left;
    transition: background 0.2s ease;
  }

  .faq-question:hover .faq-q-text {
    color: var(--color-near-black);
    opacity: 1;
  }

  .faq-q-num {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--color-gold);
    opacity: 0.7;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 28px;
  }

  .faq-q-text {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(16px, 2vw, 19px);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-near-black);
    opacity: 0.85;
    flex: 1;
    line-height: 1.4;
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
  }

  .faq-icon {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--color-gold);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    transition: transform 0.35s ease;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .faq-item.open .faq-icon {
    transform: rotate(45deg);
  }

  /* Answer */
  .faq-answer {
    max-height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: max-height 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
  }

  .faq-item.open .faq-answer {
    max-height: 800px;
  }

  .faq-answer-text {
    font-family: 'Lora', serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #666;
    padding: 0 0 28px 48px;
  }

  /* Still question */
  .faq-still {
    margin-top: 80px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: center;
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .faq-still-rule {
    width: 48px;
    height: 2px;
    background: var(--color-gold);
    opacity: 0.6;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .faq-still-heading {
    font-family: 'Lora', serif;
    font-size: clamp(26px, 3vw, 38px);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-near-black);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .faq-still-sub {
    font-family: 'Lora', serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--color-near-black);
    opacity: 0.5;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .faq-still-link {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #0e0703;
    background: var(--color-gold);
    padding: 14px 32px;
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-top: 8px;
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
  }

  .faq-still-link:hover {
    opacity: 0.85;
  }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .faq { padding: 72px 0 64px; }
    .faq-inner { padding: 0 24px; }
    .faq-answer-text { padding-left: 0; }
    .faq-header { margin-bottom: 48px; }
    .faq-q-num { display: none; }
  }
</style>

<script>
  // Accordion logic
  document.querySelectorAll('[data-faq]').forEach((item) => {
    const btn = item.querySelector('.faq-question');
    btn?.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const isOpen = item.classList.contains('open');
      // Close all
      document.querySelectorAll('[data-faq].open').forEach((other) => {
        other.classList.remove('open');
        other.querySelector('.faq-question')?.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
      });
      // Toggle current
      if (!isOpen) {
        item.classList.add('open');
        btn.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');
      }
    });
  });
</script>
